title: [SOLVED]820-3437 liquid damage
message: Hi we have an 820-3437 that did not start up. It had very small liquid damage on R5641 and R5193 near the SMC which we replaced and also no 1.05v. We replaced C7630 (one side was corroded) and wired pin 1 to pin 1 from R7630 and after this the macbook starts up. Runs fine on battery, however, then we connect the charger the screen blacks out and we do not get any light on the charger. Fan keeps spinning and as soon as we remove the charger the display turns on again. With nothing but I/O board connected the mac also boots up but no light on the charger. Could not find a short in PP3V42_G3H. The I/O board also had a tiny green spil on it, after ultrasonic still the same, replaced the board and cable, still the same. Any ideas on this one?

title: [SOLVED]820-3437 liquid damage
message: Please mark as solved. PP3V42_G3H pin 21 on J9500 was burned
